### RAG:

Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) is **a Generative AI technique that enhances LLM accuracy by fetching relevant, up-to-date information from external, trusted knowledge bases (like company databases or websites) before generating a response**. It reduces hallucinations and keeps models informed without needing expensive retraining.

Retrieve ( Find useful info)

Augement (add it io ai knowledge )

Generate ( create a better response form info retrieved and based on user query)

Docs → Chunks →Embedding model→ Vector DB (chunks + Vector) 

Seach Query →Embedding model → Embedding → search  (Vector DB)  → Retrieve top similar embeddings → LLM → Response

